<L>__{int university chapel day}
<A>__{krempe delivers the eulogy before the open casket. the chapel is full. victor is seated near the back. dazed. henry comes up the aisle and slides in next to him. victor doesn't even glance over. henry whispers:}
<C>__{henry}
<D>__{they just caught the man who did it.}
<C>__{victor}
<D>__{he was a frightened soul who acted out of fear and ignorance.}
<C>__{henry}
<D>__{they'll hang him all the same.}
<C>__{victor}
<D>__{good. i will be there to hear his worthless neck snap.}
<A>__{people glance back. henry lays his hand on victor's elbow.}
<C>__{henry}
<D>__{keep your voice down. you don't know what you're saying.}
<C>__{victor}
<D>__{it was wrong, henry! it shouldn't have happened! the bastard deserves to die.}
<A>__{victor is causing ripples of attention throughout the chapel. even krempe falters briefly in his eulogy. henry pulls victor from the pew, drags him up the aisle...}
